      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SCOOBARTIE (3) broke through for a dominant maiden win when last seen at Bendigo, ridden confidently on speed and booting away to score by three lengths. Sticking to the short course seems to be key and Brad Rawiller should give him a very similar run here from the good gate. OUR WYND CHYMES (5) is a lightly raced filly in her first preparation. She won well on debut and has been right there in two runs since in this grade. Doubt she needs to improve much at all to go one better. EDGES DIAMOND (2) resumes. He tackled some stronger races last time in and wasn't disgraced. He's still lightly raced with just eight starts and can run a bold race fresh. VEGA BLUES (4) resumes having won his maiden first up last time in. Watch for a market push. ORLABENT (1) is going okay and comes back a notch in grade here.",
